 goes out to Jzonn, since I am including his name in the note)<br>
.  <br>
What do you generally think about having different council reps go out and participate in different raids as observers and collect our findings and observations here?<br>
<br>
cheers<br>
pip<br>
<br>
====<br>
Hi and well met,<br>
<br>
Myself and another ranger named Jzonn have been inching closer and closer to the level 50 and are starting to think about the planes and their associated cute mobs.  In one of our discussions, we both discovered that we were impressed with the success and wonderous about the strategies and method employed by the Ashborne / Sacred Order of Shadows and their plane and dragon hunts.   <br>
<br>
So, to make it short, I would like to ask whether it would be possible for us to come to one of your raids as silent helpful observers.  Silent in a sense that we won't do shouts, interfere or ask for any loots, helpful in a sense that we will help with heals, dmg etc wherever we can.  I believe that we can learn a lot, and I would prefer learning before stumbling into a plane without trying to see how knowledgeable planers do it.  <br>
<br>
This request goes straight out to Vyktor, and I will also seek out Grenouille for the same request.  Let me know what you think.  Any response is appreciated, and I understand perfectly if there is a secret to your success that you don't want to tell anyone until your book release <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
Pippi Langstrump<br>
