<br>
- good communication with shouts and to group leaders, who communicated to the groups<br>
- good placement of casters (away from Vox)<br>
- people weren't too rowdy<br>
- nice CR efforts (the speediest part of the hunt)<br>
<br>
Things to think about:<br>
- speediness and promptness<br>
- more debriefing<br>
- more training<br>
- telling the people at least a day in advance what they will have to consider and bring (e.g., specific resist armor, getting bound)<br>
<br>
I guess one thing I would like to try with the next guild mixer hunts (not just the 44+) to see if we can mimic a raid situation - the mob won't be the same, but we may as well start with getting experience in organizing and setting up appropriate groups, prepping the participants the night before and right before the hunt, selecting group leads, call out the strategy and special considerations (e.g., special buffing). What do you think?<br>
